# [FIX 1] Header rows were being detected via `is.na(ref_value1) & is.na(std_rej)`,
# but ref_value1 holds "" for headers, not NA -- and is.na("") is FALSE. So
# is_header was NEVER TRUE: every header row fell through to the count branch
# and rendered as "NA (NA%)", and the bold tab_style() never fired on anything.
